Package remodel.util

Class PureSet<T>

java.lang.Object
remodel.util.PureCollection<T>
remodel.util.PureSet<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<T>
public class PureSet<T>
extends PureCollection<T>
PureSet is the ReMoDeL constructive set type. PureSet supports the constructive union, difference and intersection operations. It also supports higher-order iteration operations with Function and Predicate lambda-expressions. The set of elements is implemented as an ordered LinkedHashSet.
Version:
1.0
Author:
Anthony J H Simons

    • select

      public <S extends T> PureSet<S> select​(Predicate<T> predicate)
      Creates a new PureSet including only those elements of this set that satisfy a given predicate. The result may be of a more specific type. This supports type down-casting from sets of mixed types. The element type of the result must be inferred.
      Type Parameters:
      S - the more specific type of elements in the result.
      Parameters:
      predicate - the test to apply.
      Returns:
      a PureSet of the same type, containing elements accepted by the predicate.

    • toString

      public java.lang.String toString()
      Returns a pretty-printed String representation of this PureSet. The String is of the form: "ElemType{e1, e2, ... en}", where ElemType is the simple name of the element type, and e1..en are the pretty-printed String representation of the elements.
      Overrides:
      toString in class java.lang.Object
